cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about speech recognition using a convolutional network and graph decoding. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper discusses training the model to output letters without the need for force alignment of phonemes. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper presents an end-to-end model for speech recognition. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper uses a convolutional network for the acoustic model.
